Activities at the Senate hallowed Chamber this morning was disrupted following the heavy leaking of the roof, as cleaning crew worked tirelessly to dry out the Senate lobby at the National Assembly following heavy rains.  Water dripped from the roof of the building shortly before plenary resumed Tuesday, leaving National Assembly staff seen scooping water that flooded the lobby of the building with buckets and Packers. Some Senators were forced to go through the house of representatives in order to have access to the senate Chambers  Recall that President Muhammadu Buhari had in 2019 approved about 37 billion naira for the renovation of the National Assembly building complex. This amount generated a lot of reaction with some Nigerians saying the amount was too much for the project.